    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Crankcase, Crankshaft, and Camshaft - Removal
        - Camshaft Bushings
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s15.2.7" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Camshaft Bushings</title>
        <step1>
            <para id="s15.2.7.ref1" count="1">Determine necessity of replacing bushings based on
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_315.xml" xrefid="s15.3.5.ref1">running clearance</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s15.3.5.ref1"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450015011" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM07/M07108.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Camshaft bushing</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft bushing remover/installer (expanding collet) ZTSE4489</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Pulling screw (from camshaft bushing kit ZTSE2893A)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_325.xml" xrefid="s15.t3">camshaft bushing kit ZTSE2893A</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s15.t3"/>
                with
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_325.xml" xrefid="s15.t3">camshaft bushing remover/installer (expanding
                    collet) ZTSE4489
                </hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s15.t3"/>
                to remove all camshaft bushings. Install camshaft bushing remover/installer (expanding collet in
                collapsed state) in camshaft bushing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Hold a wrench on end of pulling screw to prevent screw from turning.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Assemble pulling screw in camshaft bushing remover/installer (expanding collet) and tighten
                backup nut until collet fits tightly in camshaft bushing. To avoid nicks on bushings, be careful when
                inserting or removing threads of pulling screw.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach pulling plate, thrust bearing, and drive nut on pulling screw. Tighten nut against
                thrust bearing and pulling plate. Continue to tighten nut on pulling screw until camshaft bushing is
                free from upper crankcase assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
